Genus 
<taxonomicName id="6E941092C694EB7AC45CA2451FB9FA3C" LSID="77028448-1ACE-58C9-A5DA-2317AB90B44B" authority="Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, new genus record for China" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Caelestomorpha Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, new genus record for China</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="288D3CD38432A894C074770C164C4D06" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="6D3A12294E5998825F181D5F9A21FC4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="70BDD9F21EEFE96DA7A8C631039132D4" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Caelestomorpha</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, Entomofauna, suppl. 16: 64. Type species (original designation): 
<taxonomicName id="4AFD265441E213CBC6F8F4360EBD991D" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha albiceris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiceris">Caelestomorpha albiceris</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009. Type locality Vietnam: Ninh 
<normalizedToken id="35A77F0694BE2DD06F78E6AB53A18B9F" originalValue="Bình">Binh</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0C9C0AEC3DB5E4D4936CCDB0C86A8354" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="33EA7123E07A3838AA2508D222CF487E" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C9E82A21559027A7039B777C6FB1C84" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="0D37BAEC9E533A05B106BF4CA1B071BE" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7ED61E85FD601494E127774C909AFD69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Caelestomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected by Solovyev and Witt in 2009, with 
<taxonomicName id="54C0AE370F5934965DFBDCE96EF46E96" genus="C." lsidName="C. albiceris" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="albiceris">
<emphasis id="AE882581E4DB469664EB7B5C2C21EB9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">C. albiceris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009 as its type species. To date, 
<taxonomicName id="82EE9D5B4EDDEBA2CB5FE441461508F3" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="82AB6E2194A9B9EAF0BCF4122966ADDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Caelestomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes only one congener 
<taxonomicName id="52ABC7E7D4E53FE812D0AA220D85184D" genus="C." lsidName="C. endodonta" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="endodonta">
<emphasis id="9CDC7CEE6E11DA7B49585629D77CA14D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">C. endodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson, 1897) besides the type species, which was transferred from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="DFC7441A182D2CBDCAAD25E2C1834DD1" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Narosa" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Narosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4524D66A07374F7AB281168E33B86B1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Narosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Walker, 1855 by 
<bibRefCitation id="B0A05A42A579E8B07F76016A4844CAF5" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. Members in this genus are of medium size, the ground colour is pale yellow with a series of dentate, almost parallel, oblique fasciae on the surface of the forewing. Of the male genitalia, the uncus is finger-shaped, blunt apically; the cucullus is densely covered with short hairs; and the vesica contains a field of cornuti (
<bibRefCitation id="8DDE64A047B8AAD2CF28AB0DD7BD4F97" author="Hampson, GF" editor="Phipson, HM" journalOrPublisher="XI. Bombay Natural History Society, Bombay" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="277 - 297" refId="B2" refString="Hampson, GF, 1897. The moths of India. Supplementary paper to the volumes in &quot;the fauna of British India&quot;. Part I. In: Phipson, HM, Ed., The Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, Vol. XI. Bombay Natural History Society, Bombay: 277 - 297" title="The moths of India. Supplementary paper to the volumes in &quot; the fauna of British India &quot;. Part I." volumeTitle="The Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, Vol." year="1897">Hampson 1897</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6B049C623D890D5B40815F91DFC1DDE3" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In this paper, the third species 
<taxonomicName id="9859B5D8769B33D03B64AFD2EEF05B2B" authorityName="Wu &amp; Solovyev &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha serratus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="1ED3A6DB215A6927AEE065F26DD055A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Caelestomorpha serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is described below and the genus is newly recorded in China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
